               <physDesc>
                  <p> The calendrical elements in the date point partly to 1 Aug. 1707, partly to
                     the next day, 2 Aug. 1707. The former day was a Friday, 14th tithi (as stated
                     in the colophon), but also the last day of the month of Āṭi (whereas the
                     colophons records the first day of the next month, Āvaṇi); the latter day
                     agrees with the colophon in terms of month and day, but it was a Saturday (not
                     a Friday) and a full moon tithi (i.e. the 15th, not the 14th tithi). In
                     addition, on both days the constellation recorded in the colophon (pūca, 8th
                     nakṣatra) is hopelessly wrong: on 1 August 1707 the current constellation was
                     the 22nd, Tiruvōṇam; on 2 August 1707 the current constellation was the 23rd,
                     Aviṭṭam. </p>
               </physDesc>
